  "text": "[TO BE PUBLISHED IN THE GAZETTE OF INDIA, EXTRAORDINARY, PART-II, SECTION-3, SUB-SECTION (i)] GOVERNMENT OF INDIA MINISTRY OF FINANCE (DEPARTMENT OF REVENUE) (CENTRAL BOARD OF EXCISE AND CUSTOMS) New Delhi, dated the 1st April, 2016 CORRIGENDUM G.S.R (E).- In the notification of the Government of India in the Ministry of Finance (Department of Revenue), No.43/2016- Customs(N.T.), dated the 31st March, 2016 published in the Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part-II, Section- 3, Sub-section (i) vide number G.S.R.378(E), dated the 31st March, 2016, the expression “tourist of Indian origin” appearing in the first proviso to Rule 3, shall be read as “tourist of foreign origin”. [F. No. 520/09/2016-CusVI] (B. Konthoujam) Under Secretary -- 1 of 1 --",
